title: Children's tooth decay, United Kingdom, 2005/06
name: Children's tooth decay, United Kingdom, 2005/06
description: Association of Public Health Observatories publishes data on children's tooth decay (at age 5). the purpose is to draw attention to areas of high tooth decay. To improve oral health in children by reducing the prevalence of dental decay. This health indicator is defined by mean number of teeth per child sampled which were either actively decayed or had been filled or extracted.
